item.title: CVE-2020-11003|2024-08-04T11:21:14.428Z -- fraction -- oasis
item.description: Oasis before version 2.15.0 has a potential DNS rebinding or CSRF vulnerability. If you're running a vulnerable application on your computer and an attacker can trick you into visiting a malicious website, they could use DNS rebinding and CSRF attacks to read/write to vulnerable applications. This has been patched in 2.15.0.
